---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Pre & Post-natal Women"
	description="Expert women's health physiotherapy through every stage of pregnancy and postnatal recovery. Pelvic girdle pain, pelvic floor rehab, diastasis recti and return to exercise — in a safe, private space."
>
	<PageHero
		title="Post-natal Women"
		highlight="Pre &"
		subtitle="Expert knowledge and compassionate care at every stage, from early pregnancy through to long-term postnatal recovery."
		breadcrumb="Pre & Post-natal Women"
	/>

	<ImageText
		eyebrow="Through every stage"
		heading="Specialist care for"
		highlight="every stage"
		image="/womens-health.jpg"
		imageAlt="Women's health physiotherapy"
	>
		<p>Pregnancy and the postnatal period place extraordinary demands on the female body. At Balance, our women's health specialists provide expert knowledge and compassionate care at every stage, from early pregnancy through to long-term postnatal recovery.</p>
		<p>Pelvic girdle pain, lower back pain, sciatica and postural changes are extremely common during pregnancy and all highly treatable. Our physiotherapists and osteopaths manage these conditions safely and effectively, keeping you as comfortable and active as possible throughout.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		eyebrow="Pelvic floor health"
		heading="A safe, private"
		highlight="space"
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/condition/womens-pelvic-health/pregnant-belly.jpg"
		imageAlt="Expectant mother holding her bump"
	>
		<p>Pelvic floor health is central to our service. Whether preparing for birth, recovering from delivery or healing after a caesarean, our specialists provide thorough assessment and tailored rehabilitation.</p>
		<p>Pelvic floor dysfunction is far more common than many women realise, and far more treatable. We provide a safe, private and non-judgmental space to address these concerns properly.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		eyebrow="Postnatal recovery"
		heading="Rebuild strength. Restore"
		highlight="energy."
		image="/physio/body-3.jpg"
		imageAlt="Postnatal rehabilitation at Balance Physio"
	>
		<p>Postnatal recovery is about rebuilding strength, restoring energy and feeling like yourself again. Graduated exercise programmes, diastasis recti rehabilitation and return-to-sport guidance are all available, with our studios and gym accessible daily at your own pace.</p>
		<p>You deserve expert, joined-up care that supports not just your body, but your confidence and energy for life.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
